# Phase 4: MD Parser

This branch implements Phase 4 - Markdown portfolio import parser.

See issue #3 for details.

## Status: ✅ COMPLETE

## Deliverables

- [x] MDParserProtocol.swift - Protocol definition with configuration options
- [x] MDParser.swift - Full implementation with table and list format support
- [x] MDParserError.swift - Comprehensive error types with LocalizedError
- [x] PortfolioConfig.swift - Sendable data structures for parsed configuration
- [x] test-md-parser.swift - Test script with 8 test cases
- [x] example-portfolio.md - Full format example
- [x] example-portfolio-simple.md - List format example

## Features

- Parse portfolio name from h1 header
- Parse metadata (risk profile, expected return, max drawdown, frequency)
- Parse target allocation tables
- Parse positions from table or list format
- Market inference from symbol suffixes
- Support for US, HK, and CN markets
- Bilingual support (Chinese and English)

## Supported Markdown Formats

### Full Table Format
```markdown
# Portfolio Name
- 风险偏好: moderate
- 预期收益: 8%
- 最大回撤: 15%
- 调仓频率: quarterly

## 目标配置
| 代码 | 比例 |
| AAPL | 40% |
| MSFT | 35% |

## 持仓
| 代码 | 名称 | 类型 | 市场 | 数量 | 成本 |
| AAPL | Apple | stock | US | 100 | 150.0 |
| 0700.HK | Tencent | stock | HK | 200 | 380.5 |
```

### Simple List Format
```markdown
# Simple Portfolio
- riskProfile: conservative

## Positions
- AAPL: 100 shares @ $150.0
- MSFT: 50 shares @ $300.0
```

## Usage

```swift
let parser = MDParser()
let config = try parser.parse(markdownContent)

// Create CoreData entities from config
let portfolio = Portfolio(context: context)
portfolio.name = config.name
portfolio.riskProfile = config.riskProfile ?? .moderate
// ...
```

